\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Define 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{i_{1}\ldots i_{n}}$
\end_inset

 to be the sign of 
\begin_inset Formula $(i_{1},\ldots,i_{n})$
\end_inset

 if it is a permutation, and 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 otherwise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is, 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{i_{1}\ldots i_{n}}=\mbox{det}(\delta_{i_{1}},\ldots,\delta_{i_{n}})$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

