\begin_layout Subsection
Some assumptions about volumes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We assume the Cavalieri principle, that is volumes are shear invariant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And we assume that volumes are invariant to translations.
 that is, it is homogeneous in every variable.
